{
  "solution": "The combined velocity change required at apogee is calculated using the plane change equation for vector subtraction: Δv = √(v_a² + v_c² - 2 v_a v_c cos(Δi)). Given v_a = 1933 m/s, v_c = 3058 m/s, and Δi = 19.7°, first find cos(19.7°) ≈ 0.9415. Then compute v_a² = (1933)² = 3,736,489 m²/s², v_c² = (3058)² = 9,351,364 m²/s², so v_a² + v_c² = 13,087,853 m²/s². Compute 2 v_a v_c cos(Δi) = 2 × 1933 × 3058 × 0.9415 ≈ 11,130,627.66 m²/s². Thus, Δv² = 13,087,853 - 11,130,627.66 = 1,957,225.34 m²/s², and Δv = √(1,957,225.34) ≈ 1399 m/s.",
