{
  "solution": "First, compute the cross product components c₁, c₂, c₃ using the given formulas: c₁ = a₂b₃ - a₃b₂, c₂ = a₃b₁ - a₁b₃, c₃ = a₁b₂ - a₂b₁. With the provided values: a₁=0.572267, a₂=0.334664, a₃=0.212628; b₁=0.339116, b₂=0.484508, b₃=0.523339, we calculate: c₁ = 0.334664×0.523339 - 0.212628×0.484508 = 0.072123, c₂ = 0.212628×0.339116 - 0.572267×0.523339 = -0.227384, c₃ = 0.572267×0.484508 - 0.334664×0.339116 = 0.163778. Next, compute the latitude of the first node: lat₁ = arctan(c₃ / √(c₁² + c₂²)). √(c₁² + c₂²) = √(0.072123² + (-0.227384)²) = 0.238548. Then c₃/√(c₁² + c₂²) = 0.163778/0.238548 = 0.686568, so lat₁ = arctan(0.686568) = 34.46°. For the longitude: long₁ = arctan(c₁/c₂) + 90°. c₁/c₂ = 0.072123/(-0.227384) = -0.31718, so arctan(-0.31718) = -17.59°, thus long₁ = -17.59° + 90° = 72.41°. The second intersection node has opposite latitude and is 180° away in longitude: lat₂ = -lat₁ = -34.46°, long₂ = long₁ + 180° = 72.41° + 180° = 252.41°.",
  "final answer": "Latitude = -34.46°, Longitude = 252.41°"
