{
  "solution": "The magnitude of the vector r₂ is calculated using the formula |r₂| = √(x² + y² + z²), where x, y, and z are the components of the vector. Given r₂ = -0.446838X + 1.593577Y + -0.057117Z AU, so x = -0.446838 AU, y = 1.593577 AU, z = -0.057117 AU. Compute x² = (-0.446838)² = 0.199664198244, y² = (1.593577)² = 2.539487654929, z² = (-0.057117)² = 0.003262351689. Sum these: 0.199664198244 + 2.539487654929 + 0.003262351689 = 2.742414204862. Then |r₂| = √2.742414204862 ≈ 1.656024 AU after rounding to six decimal places.",
