{
  "solution": "The second transfer orbit in the bi-elliptic transfer has its pericenter at the final circular orbit radius r3 = 206512 km and its apocenter at the intermediate point r2 = 971224 km. The semi-major axis a is calculated as a = (r_p + r_a)/2 = (206512 + 971224)/2 = 588868 km. The specific mechanical energy ε is given by ε = -μ / (2a), where μ = 398600.5 km³/s² is the gravitational parameter. Substituting the values, ε = -398600.5 / (2 × 588868) = -398600.5 / 1177736 ≈ -0.338446 km²/s².",
  "final answer": "-0.338446 km²/s²"
